[b]Tweezer & Kangaroo Zones[/b] detects two specific reversal candlestick patterns — tweezer tops/bottoms and kangaroo tails (pin bars) — and converts them into scored supply and demand zones that persist and decay over time.

[b]What it does[/b]

Where most candlestick indicators just mark the pattern and move on, this script uses the detected pattern as the origin point for a dynamic zone. The zone is scored on formation and that score decays as bars pass without the level being tested. Overlapping zones are merged. The result is a living map of supply and demand levels grounded in actual rejection events.

[b]Features[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Pattern detection[/b] — Tweezer tops/bottoms and kangaroo tails with timeframe-sensitive sensitivity settings
[*][b]Zone scoring[/b] — 5-component score (0–100) per zone based on candle characteristics, context, and location
[*][b]Freshness decay[/b] — Zone scores decrease as bars pass without a test, filtering out stale levels
[*][b]Top-N filtering[/b] — Only the highest-scoring active zones are displayed
[*][b]Zone merging[/b] — Overlapping zones are consolidated to reduce clutter
[*][b]Structure context[/b] — HH/HL/LH/LL swing detection for directional bias
[*][b]HTF stack panel[/b] — Up to 3 timeframes displayed in a summary panel
[*][b]Confluence scoring[/b] — 8-component system for evaluating zone quality in context
[/list]

